{
  "stem": "25591.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I didn't have a personal meeting with him, as such.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He came to visit the houses, and I was part of a group that greeted him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I found him enormously inspirational.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I really felt he was larger than life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think I sensed what he was doing more than I understood what he was doing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, he really left behind the comfort and luxury and safety of Sweden and came to the hell that Budapest was in the summer of 1944, because he felt a common bond with human beings who were of a different ethnicity, different religion, different background, different situation from him.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he felt a personal obligation to help.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And quite frankly, he has been the dominant theme of my life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He has been the dominant influence on my life more than anybody else, more than my parents, more than any friends, more than any teachers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If-- if-- if I am asked, at the end of my life, who is the person who shaped you and your values and your actions and your views and your energies, it's Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I-- I-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I have his [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] photo and his large facsimile of the stamp we-- we'll soon see in every post office.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I have a large sign saying 'Wallenberg Way' that Washington gave me as a-- a-- a remembrance of the fact that the Holocaust Museum is on Wallenberg Place.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And of course, Wallenberg tied the lives of my wife and my own life together, because she has devoted years of her life to Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
